# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the airuse-improved project following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- **Added dependency**: `@vercel/speed-insights@2.0.0` to package.json
- **Updated lock file**: package-lock.json now includes all Speed Insights dependencies (153 packages)

### 2. Speed Insights Script Created
- **Created**: `frontend/public/js/speed-insights.js`
  - Implements the Speed Insights initialization script for vanilla JavaScript
  - Injects the Vercel Speed Insights tracking script from `https://va.vercel-scripts.com/v1/speed-insights/script.js`
  - Includes proper error handling and prevents duplicate script injection
  - Uses IIFE pattern to avoid polluting global namespace

### 3. HTML Files Updated
Added `<script src="js/speed-insights.js" defer></script>` to all 8 HTML pages:
- `frontend/public/index.html` (landing page)
- `frontend/public/builder.html` (resume builder)
- `frontend/public/dashboard.html` (user dashboard)
- `frontend/public/login.html` (login page)
- `frontend/public/signup.html` (signup page)
- `frontend/public/forgot-password.html` (password reset)
- `frontend/public/privacy.html` (privacy policy)
- `frontend/public/terms.html` (terms of service)

### 4. Content Security Policy (CSP) Updated
Modified `backend/server.js` to allow Speed Insights:
- **scriptSrc**: Added `va.vercel-scripts.com` to allow the Speed Insights script to load
- **connectSrc**: Added `*.vercel-scripts.com` and `vercel.live` to allow Speed Insights to send performance data to Vercel

## Implementation Details

### Framework Detection
This project uses vanilla JavaScript (not Next.js, React, Vue, or other frameworks), so the implementation follows the vanilla/other frameworks approach from the Vercel documentation.

### How It Works
1. When each HTML page loads, the `speed-insights.js` script executes
2. The script initializes the Speed Insights queue (`window.si` and `window.siq`)
3. It dynamically creates a script element pointing to Vercel's Speed Insights CDN
4. The script is injected into the page head with the `defer` attribute
5. Once loaded, Speed Insights automatically tracks Core Web Vitals and other performance metrics

### Security
- All Speed Insights domains are properly whitelisted in the Content Security Policy
- Script loading includes error handling to gracefully handle content blockers
- Uses defer attribute to prevent blocking page rendering

## Next Steps for Users

After deployment to Vercel:
1. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel dashboard:
   - Navigate to your project settings
   - Select "Speed Insights" from the sidebar
   - Click "Enable" button
2. Deploy the changes to Vercel
3. Visit your site to verify the tracking script loads (check browser DevTools Network tab for requests to `va.vercel-scripts.com`)
4. Monitor performance metrics in the Vercel Speed Insights dashboard

